The Khlum wind pump is a local technical monument.
It is a bit of a memento of the present: it reminds us of the time when local people fought for quality drinking water.
The one in Chlum in the past centuries was a rarity.
It was not until 1910 that Khlum deputies decided on a solution that would suit them until the mid-1980s.
In the village at the branch to <0xC4><0x8C><0xC3><0xAD>chov, they dug a seven-meter-deep well.
