The statements of a brilliant scientist of the last century will probably never cease to fascinate mankind.
He was able to dive so deep into everything that the product was always a stunning discovery.
Albert Einstein (1879-1955) was one of the greatest scientists of all time.
He entered the consciousness of people primarily through his special and general theory of relativity, which so far best describes the universe in its gigantic ratio.
It is also impossible to forget his explanation of the photoelectric effect or the idea of quantization of the electromagnetic field.
There is no doubt that the description itself and the system of knowledge of the popular theory of relativity are so intricate for many people that they prefer easy adaptations for closer acquaintance.
But it is not easy.
But it would not be Albert Einstein if he did not find a brilliantly simplified form of explanation for this: A watch near your beloved seems a minute; a minute in a hot oven seems an hour - and that is relativity.
I took the liberty of choosing from his entire list of famous quotes these ten that literally captivated me.
Intelligent people try to solve problems, geniuses try not to do them.
Only two things are infinite.
Space and human stupidity.
I'm not so sure about the first one.
No amount of experimentation can ever prove me right.
But only he can prove me wrong at any time.
But it is a sad time when it is easier to break an atom than to destroy prejudice.
If the mess on the table is a reflection of the mess in the mind, what then reflects the empty table?
I don't know what he's going to fight in World War III, but in World War IV, it's going to be sticks and stones.
There are thousands of ways to kill time, but no way to resurrect it.
To know little is dangerous, and to know much is dangerous.
If I had an hour to master the problem on which my life depended, I would spend 40 minutes studying it, 15 minutes analyzing it, and 5 minutes solving it.
The hardest thing in the world to understand is income tax.
Finally, I cannot forgive myself for not including Einstein’s formula for success: If we take A for success, the formula is: A=X+Y+Z, where X is work, Y is rest, and Z is holding your tongue.
